#: ../../../reference/config_files/conanrc.rst:11
msgid ""
"The **.conanrc** file can be placed in the folder where you are running "
"Conan or any parent folder. This file is used to set up the Conan user home "
"directory by defining the `conan_home` value. This value will take "
"precedence over the :ref:`CONAN_HOME "
"<reference_environment_variables_conan_home>` environment variable in case "
"it's also defined. Below are some examples of how you can define the Conan "
"user home in the **.conanrc** file:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/config_files/conanrc.rst:18
msgid "Set the Conan home to an absolute folder:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/config_files/conanrc.rst:20
msgid ""
"# accepts comments\n"
"conan_home=/absolute/folder"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/config_files/conanrc.rst:25
msgid "Set the Conan home to a relative folder inside the current folder:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/config_files/conanrc.rst:27
msgid "conan_home=./relative/folder/inside/current/folder"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/config_files/conanrc.rst:31
msgid "Set the Conan home to a relative folder outside the current folder:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/config_files/conanrc.rst:33
msgid "conan_home=../relative/folder/outside/current/folder"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/config_files/conanrc.rst:37
msgid ""
"Set the Conan home to a path containing the `~` symbol, which will be "
"expanded to the system's user home:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/config_files/conanrc.rst:39
msgid "conan_home=~/use/the/user/home/to/expand/it"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/config_files/conanrc.rst:43
msgid ""
"Be aware that the **.conanrc** file is searched for in all parent folders. "
"For example, in this structure:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/config_files/conanrc.rst:46
msgid ""
".\n"
".conanrc\n"
"|-- project1\n"
"|-- project2"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/config_files/conanrc.rst:54
msgid ""
"If you are running from the folder `project1`, the parent folders are "
"traversed recursively until a **.conanrc** file is found, in case it exists."
msgstr ""
